727244f-a.title: Queens: Linden Place - 32nd Avenue
727244f-a.text:
Linden Place, at the N.E. corner of 32nd Avenue, formerly
Myrtle Avenue, showing a frame dwelling with a lookout tower.
This type of home was popular in the latter half of the nine-
teenth century. Also shown is the north side of 32nd Avenue,
extending east to 137th Street.
P. L. Sperr  March 3, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
